               <p>Hanby became a <seg ana="itinerancy">traveling preacher</seg> in <date when="1754"
                     >1754</date> and served in <placeName>Staffordshire</placeName>,
                     <placeName>Northumberland</placeName>, and other northern circuits. In <date
                     when="1785">1785</date>
                  <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> ordained him as an
                  elder for Methodist work in <placeName>Scotland</placeName>, and he presided at
                  the <date when="1794">1794</date> Conference. See Atmore, <hi rend="italic"
                     >Memorial</hi>, 179–81; <hi rend="italic">DEB</hi>, 513; <hi rend="italic"
                     >EMP</hi>, 2:131–57; <hi rend="italic">Minutes</hi> (post-Wesley, <date
                     when="1797">1797</date>), 1:380; and Vickers, <hi rend="italic"
                  >Dictionary</hi>, 148.</p>
